# Supply Chain Security

Every dependency entering this project MUST be pinned to an exact, reproducible version with integrity verification.

## Go Modules

- All versions in `go.mod` MUST be exact (no `>=`, no `latest`). Go enforces this by design.
- `go.sum` MUST be committed and MUST pass `go mod verify` before every commit.
- Run `go mod tidy` before committing to prune unused dependencies.
- NEVER run `GONOSUMCHECK=*` or `GONOSUMDB=*` — all modules must be verified against the Go checksum database.
- When adding a dependency, verify it is actively maintained and has no known CVEs: `govulncheck ./...`

## Docker Images

- All `FROM` lines in `Dockerfile` MUST include a `@sha256:` digest after the tag.
- All `image:` lines in `docker-compose.yml` MUST use `@sha256:` digests, never `:latest`.
- To update an image: pull the new tag, extract the digest with `docker inspect --format='{{index .RepoDigests 0}}'`, and replace the digest in the file.

## CDN / External Scripts

- Every `<script src>` or `<link href>` loading from a CDN MUST include:
  1. An exact version in the URL (e.g., `@2.19.0`)
  2. An `integrity="sha384-..."` attribute (SRI)
  3. `crossorigin="anonymous"`
- Generate SRI: `curl -s <URL> | openssl dgst -sha384 -binary | openssl base64 -A`
- NEVER use unversioned CDN paths that resolve to `latest`.

## Pre-Commit Enforcement

A git pre-commit hook at `scripts/pre-commit` runs automatically. It checks:
1. `go mod tidy` — no stale deps
2. `go mod verify` — checksum integrity
3. `go vet ./...` — code correctness
4. Unused imports (via `goimports -l`)
5. Docker digest presence in `Dockerfile` and `docker-compose.yml`
6. Forbidden `:latest` / `@latest` references in operational files
7. SRI attributes on all external `<script>` tags

If any check fails, the commit is blocked. NEVER bypass with `--no-verify` unless explicitly discussed.

## Adding New Dependencies

1. Check the package on pkg.go.dev for maintenance status
2. `go get <pkg>@<exact-version>`
3. `go mod tidy`
4. `go mod verify`
5. `govulncheck ./...` (if installed)
6. Commit `go.mod` and `go.sum` together
